LINE.Text: There aren't any fans in the world like college football fans.
They are loyal, spirited, and apparently very social We took a look at
the 20 colleges with the most Facebook likes, and compared those to
their Twitter following, school enrollment size, and how all of that
matches up to Heisman winners and national championships
Twitter and Facebook have changed the way fans connect with one
another and the teams they support. It also makes the competit tive
banter on game day louder and clearer Powerhouses on the field
seem to align with socia ollowing, as some of the biggest names
in college footbal have the strongest followings on these social
networks Want more ollowers and likes? Post more wins.
Bigger isn't always better when it comes to college football.
We found that the mid-sized the -sized schools seem to produce more
championships and Heisman winners than the campuses that boast
the largest student bodies. While there aren't ever any guarantees
for students with footbal careers in their sights, the bigger fish
might be found in the somewhat smaller ponds,
